<br>
Personally, I lean slightly towards us not bailing them out.<br>
<br>
In the case of airlines, it's not like <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>all</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> airlines are suffering.  In fact, many of the smaller ones are doing quite well.  I don't think it's fair or reasonable that money is given to the big inefficient ones to help them compete with the smaller more efficient ones.  There's a lot of jobs to be lost, but they'll come back again, just not for United / Delta / etc.<br>
<br>
In the case of automobiles... I drive a Chevy... but let's face it, only because it's affordable.  If there weren't tariffs on imports I would definately be driving a Honda or a Volkswagen or a Subaru.  I feel like rather than supporting our car industry, the government is preventing buyers like me from buying better, safer cars <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I think our car companies have the ability to produce cars that are on par with other countries, but the safety net our government gives them prevents them from having to strive that far.  Again, there's a lot of jobs to be lost, and unlike airlines probably not all of them recoverable, but I think in the long run American car companies would learn to compete, and I could drive a car that doesn't sound like a bucket of bolts when I turn over the engine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=siava>Siava</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.knology.net/~ahnmei/savepoint.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm an Asshat lady. <br>
