<br>
Smaller airlines have less seating capacity (with their fleet as a whole), which means not everybody who travels as a part of their job requirement will get a seat to fly to their destination. I'm assuming occupations requiring excessive travel (not uncommon) rely on major airlines because they're much more dependable. I'm not quite sure how the major ones are inefficient though. Could you explain, please?<br>
<br>
Personally, I don't like how much money is being given to the industry by the government. I *do* feel it's extreme, but on the same note, I couldn't imagine what would happen should they not receive any money whatsoever. Saying people can just get other jobs or new ones is much easier said than done. That many jobs lost would have a major impact on the economy because the major airlines employ sooooo many people. <br>
<br>
As for cars, I totally agree. Our cars could be much better and should be. <br>
<br>
