<br>
Personally, I think we are bloated on these industries.  But allowing them to fail might cause cascade effects in the economy.<br>
<br>
But let's face facts - there are Airports EVERYWHERE.  I lived in Memphis for two years or so.  There are at least FOUR International Airports within a 2-3 hour drive of Memphis.  Now, Memphis is no huge metropolis like a NY or LA...  Do you really need to fly to or from Jackson, MS?<br>
<br>
We have too much airline capacity for our needs.<br>
<br>
